<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7431.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gummeré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-03"><hi rend="italic">July 3,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(States that the British minister confirms that Kaid Maclean, the British
                            officer in the employ of the Sultan who has been negotiating with
                            Raisuli, has been seized by the latter and is being held prisoner.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>